FIELD.name: CIG Name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: CIG Name in KIG catalogue

FIELD.name: RA J2000
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Right Ascension J2000 (Leon and Verdes-Montenegro 2003)

FIELD.name: DEC J2000
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Declination J2000 (Leon and Verdes-Montenegro 2003)

FIELD.name: RA B1950
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Right Ascension B1950 (Leon and Verdes-Montenegro 2003)

FIELD.name: DEC B1950
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Declination 1950 (Leon and Verdes-Montenegro 2003)

FIELD.name: MB
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Blue absolute magnitude compiled from CGCG in (Verdes-Montenegro et al. 2005)

FIELD.name: mB-corr
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Blue corrected magnitude calculated as mB-corr = mB + AV + Ag + Ai+AK (Verdes-Montenegro et al. 2005)

FIELD.name: LB
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Blue luminosity calculated from D and mB-corr (Verdes-Montenegro et al. 2005) as explained in Lisenfeld et al. 2007

FIELD.name: Vr
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Recession Velocity (Verdes-Montenegro et al. 2005)

FIELD.name: V3K
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: 3K corrected recession Velocity (Verdes-Montenegro et al. 2005)

FIELD.name: Distance
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Distance (Verdes-Montenegro et al. 2005)

FIELD.name: Morph
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Morphological type (letter) Hubble type determined in Sulentic et al. 2006, coded in the RC3 system for galaxies with vR greater than 1000 km/s. When a type could not be assigned a code "Un" (Uncertain) is given. For galaxies with vR lower than 1000 km/s, different morphological types have been compiled from the bibliography (Sulentic et al. 2006, Table 4) which do not fit RC3 codification. We provide a bibliographic code in parentheses corresponding to the references listed in footnote 2 of Table 4 in Sulentic et al. 2006. We have not selected a preferred type when several were available, but provided all of them.

FIELD.name: Morph rc3
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Numeric morphological type (code) Hubble type determined in Sulentic et al. 2006 Table 3, coded in the RC3 system for galaxies with vR greater than 1000 km/s. For galaxies with vR lower than 1000 km/s, different morphological types have been compiled from the bibliography (Sulentic et al. 2006, Table 4) which do not fit RC3 codification. We provide a bibliographic code in parentheses corresponding to the references listed in footnote 2 of Table 4 in Sulentic et al. 2006. We have not selected a preferred type when several were available, but provided all of them.

FIELD.name: Conf morph
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Morphology confirmation A code "y" indicates that the assigned type is uncertain and there is a need for better imaging data.

FIELD.name: Bar
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Presence of a Bar A code "y" indicates secure presence and a "n" clear absence of a bar.

FIELD.name: Int
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Interacting A code "y" indicates a morphologically distorted system and/or almost certain interacting system while "-" indicates evidence for interaction/asymmetry with/without certain detection of a companion.

FIELD.name: LFIR
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: FIR luminosity, calculated as describe in Lisenfeld et al. 2007. Upper limits are indicatedwith - in front of the value. Galaxy without data points (in total: 20 objects) lie in the area not covered by IRAS.

FIELD.name: ULFIR
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Flux density upper limit code (Lisenfeld et al. 2007) 1: LFIR luminosity is an upper limit 0: LFIR liminosity has been measured

FIELD.name: F12
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Flux Density at 12um. calculated as Lisenfeld et al. 2007

FIELD.name: UL12
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Upper limit code at 12 um. (Lisenfeld et al. 2007) 1: Flux density is an upper limit 0: Flux density has been measured

FIELD.name: rms12
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: RMS noise of the data at 12um. Upper limits are preceded by a "-'' sign, and for most cases a 3sigma value has been adopted, except forCIG 397. For CIG 397 the 12um scan presents confusion with a close star and 20% of the peak of the emission has been adopted as upper limit. (Lisenfeld et al. 2007)

FIELD.name: M12
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Method used to derive F12 in Lisenfeld et al. 2007 Codes 1 to 4 correspond to the following flux estimators: 1 = Templ, 2 = Peak 3 = fnu(t), 4 = fnu(z). Code 5 corresponds to upper limits obtained as 3 sigma. Code 6 is reserved for some particular cases: CIG 397 (*) and 9 galaxies (**) present in the catalog of large optical galaxies of Rice et al. (1988) where we have used the values given in their catalog. (*) For CIG 397 the 12um scan presents confusion with a closer star an 20% of the peak of the emission has been adopted. (**) CIG 105, CIG 197, CIG 324, CIG 347, CIG 461, CIG 523, CIG 559 and CIG 610

FIELD.name: E12
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Detected galaxies are flagged with "y'' if they have been classified as extended, and with "n'' when classified as point sources. (Lisenfeld et al. 2007)

FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Factor 3 radio excess (corrected with the FIRST study). 1 if the galaxy present radio excess above a factor 3, 0 if not. (Sabater et al. 2008)
